  "text": "In the PCR-Dot Blot technique an initial PCR step, in which the DNA region of interest is amplified, is followed with dot-blotting of the products onto nylon membranes which are then probed with allele specific digoxigeninlabelled oligonucleotides. A stringent washing procedure precedes the detection of bound oligos using alkaline phosphatase-conjugated anti-digoxigenin antibodies. Membranes are exposed to chemiluminescent sensitive films and scored visually [CITATION_1] .",
